Package fr.cnrs.iees.graph.impl

Class ALGraph<N extends ALNode,​E extends ALEdge>

java.lang.Object
fr.cnrs.iees.graph.impl.ALGraph<N,​E>
Type Parameters:
N - The implementation of Node used in this graph (ALNode or a sub-class)
E - The implementation of Edge used in this graph (ALEdge or a sub-class)
All Implemented Interfaces:
EdgeSet<E>, Graph<N,​E>, NodeSet<N>, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Textable
public class ALGraph<N extends ALNode,​E extends ALEdge> extends Object implements Graph<N,​E>

A graph implemented as an adjacency list (hence the "AL" prefix). An adjacency list stores the list of edges of every node in the graph. In this implementation, each graph node stores a list of IN or OUT edges (cf. the Direction enum), i.e. it is a directed graph by default.

This implementation requires that nodes and edges are ALNodes and ALEdges or any descendant class.

Author:
Jacques Gignoux - 10 mai 2019
